==Finnish==
{{Finnish index|tu}}

===Demonstrative pronoun===
'''tuo''' (''stem'' '''tuo-''')

# [[that]]

====Declension====
The case suffixes are regular and the stem is invariant. [[Abessive]], [[comitative]] and [[instructive]] forms don't exist.

====See also====
*[[ne#Finnish|ne]]
*[[nuo#Finnish|nuo]]
*[[nämä#Finnish|nämä]]
*[[se#Finnish|se]]
*[[tämä#Finnish|tämä]]

===Verb form===
'''tuo''' (second person sg. present imperative, and part of sg. present indicative negative of ''[[tuoda]]'')

# [[bring]]

===Usage===
* ''Tuo minulle kynä. (Bring me a pen.)''
* ''Hän ei tuo minulle kynää. (He doesn't bring me a pen.)''

----

==Italian==

===Possessive adjective===
(''before the noun''): '''il tuo''' ''m'' (''f'' '''la [[tua]]''', ''m plural'' '''i [[tuoi]]''', ''f plural'' '''le [[tue]]''')<br>
(''after the noun; also used before a noun denoting a close family member''): '''tuo''' ''m'' (''f'' '''tua''', ''m plural'' '''tuoi''', ''f plural'' '''tue''')

#[[your]] (''informal form'')
#:''i tuoi figli'' - your children<!--masculine plural example before noun-->
#:''le tue macchine'' - your cars<!--feminine plural example before noun-->
#:''casa tua'' - your house<!--feminine singular example after noun-->
#:''tuo padre'' - your father<!--masculine singular example before close family member-->

===Pronoun===
'''il tuo''' ''m'' (''f'' '''la tua''', ''m plural'' '''i tuoi''', ''f plural'' '''le tue''')

#[[yours]]
#:''Sono i tuoi'' - They are yours.

